  "texts": [
    "This approach is particularly pertinent given the increasing complexity of hardware systems, which complicates the task of static WCET analysis.In addition, unlike previous studies focused on embedded systems [41,79,87,88,20], this research specifically addresses the challenges of robotic libraries.",
    "Due to their extensive use and large input spaces, there is a need for advanced WCET analysis in this context.",
    "Furthermore, the methodology adopts a blackbox approach, requiring only the software's input format, unlike other approaches that necessitate detailed hardware or software knowledge [87,100,101,88,97,20].",
    "Lee et al. [90] utilize GA and ML to determine the WCET of the QNX Neutrino, leveraging a simulator for their experiments.",
    "Similarly, Shah et al. [99] also employ GA and ML techniques, with the aid of a simulator to generate their dataset."
  ],
